==English==
===Etymology===
A [[New Testament]] name, one of the [[apostle]]s; from [[Aramaic]] ''teoma'' twin

===Proper noun===
'''Thomas'''
# An [[English]], [[French]], [[German]] and [[Dutch]] [[surname]] of [[biblical]] origin
# A [[male]] [[given name]] of the same origin - (diminutive: [[Tom]], [[Tommy]])
===Noun===
'''Thomas'''
#''(derogatory)'' An [[infidel]] (used by Christians in reference to the Apostle mentioned above not believing that Jesus had risen from the dead)

